# Pub/Sub
Example illustrating the GCP Pub/Sub nodes.

Click on the `Hello World` Inject node which will publish
a string payload message to the topic.

This will result in a message being published which
will be received by the corresponding Pub/Sub input node
which will write it to the debug output.

You must create a GCP Pub/Sub topic and a subscription
in your GCP project and enter those values in
the Pub/Sub node configurations.
